Zanzibar to Introduce VAT
DAR ES SALAAM , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Zanzibar plans to carry out the Value Added Tax ( VAT ) system starting from January 1 next year .
The new tax , to be applied at a standard rate of 20 percent , will replace sales tax and several other levies on commodities or services , the East African weekly said Monday .
The tax is expected to boost revenue significantly in Zanzibar which suffers from financial constraints .
The Zanzibar Revenue Board has started the process for VAT registration which may involve some 1,500 firms at the initial stage , the paper said .
The mainland of Tanzania carried out VAT system in July 1 this year , which has successfully increased government revenue .
